If you create a new language, remember to complete the following steps:

1) Create a suitable language directory under po with the official language
   code, e.g. "fr" for French

2)

…

n) Create a file named lang.config in your language subdirectory with the
   following content (this example uses the hypothetical case of English):
langcode="en"
langname="English"
langname_translated="English"
hint1=", "
hint2="strings missing until 80%"
langmail="English <debian-l10n-english@lists.debian.org>"

n+1) copy and adapt license.add, translate-dates.pl and generate-addendum.sh

n+2) If addenda does not (yet) work, create noaddendum in the language
   directory

n+3) In public, create …
